responses: {"Q0":"At first I tried to see if the specific shape was coming up in the same point of the line up each time. Then I mostly tried to picture the specific shape as each image was shown in order to press more correctly when that image did show up. I have a habit in studies like these of pressing buttons because I get too excited or I find myself thinking \"its gonna be the next one\" and press even if its not. So far the best way I've found to \"flash\" the actual image in my head (or say the word allowed if its a word-based one) each time and press when what I am thinking lines up with what I am seeing. I hope that makes sense!"}

{"[object Object]":"The reason I started wondering if the shape was coming at the same time in the sequence was because it felt as if I was pressing at the same time each round. That's when I first started to count the shapes that passed until I needed to press."}
